Mark's a nice guy. Didn't like the class though, histories of sciences tend to be a hit or miss. Don't take hps110

Mark and Marga are excellent professors who truly care about their students. Lectures are informational but sometimes rushed at the end - however slides are posted for your convenience. Test 1 is not hard; questions are provided beforehand and will also be on the exam. Test 2 is a take-home test. Overall great prof; only downside are the TAs.
Seems like a nice guy. But I fell the course content is very disorganised. Also the class content is an unfair representation of the tests. Nothing to do with Mark but worst TA I've ever had.
Clearly passionate about course material, but does not go very in-depth due to the volume covered in lecture.

rComments: Super sweet, and willing to go out of his way to help. Clearly interested in his material, and his enthusiasm is contagious.
Very helpful, and friendly. Extremely vivid in lecture.
LOVED HIM! Best prof in the stowe gullen stream by far. I would definitely take his other classes!

Mark is supportive and approachable. He will let you do your own thing and provide helpful feedback along the way. Sometimes he loses focus a little when leading class discussions, and on occasion his insights into material seemed a little superficial, but overall he is an very solid professor.
An excellent Prof - very interested in the course material and in the class. Approachable and pleasant.
